Certainly! Here's a clean JavaScript function to capitalize the first letter of each word in a string:

```javascript
function capitalizeWords(sentence) {
  return sentence
    .split(' ') // Split the sentence into an array of words
    .map(word => {
      if (word.length === 0) return ''; // Handle empty strings from multiple spaces
      return word.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + word.slice(1).toLowerCase();
    }) // Capitalize first letter, lowercase rest
    .join(' '); // Join the words back into a sentence
}

// Example usage:
console.log(capitalizeWords('hello world'));       // Hello World
console.log(capitalizeWords('this is a test'));    // This Is A Test
console.log(capitalizeWords('jAVAscript coding')); // Javascript Coding
```
