Happy to help! Here's a C# function to check for palindromes, handling spaces and case-insensitivity:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Linq;

public static class PalindromeChecker
{
    public static bool IsPalindrome(string text)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(text)) return true;

        // Remove non-alphanumeric characters and convert to lowercase
        string cleanedText = new string(text.Where(char.IsLetterOrDigit).ToArray()).ToLower();

        for (int i = 0; i < cleanedText.Length / 2; i++)
        {
            if (cleanedText[i] != cleanedText[cleanedText.Length - 1 - i])
            {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

// Example usage:
Console.WriteLine($"'Racecar' is a palindrome: {PalindromeChecker.IsPalindrome("Racecar")}"); // True
Console.WriteLine($"'A man, a plan, a canal: Panama' is a palindrome: {PalindromeChecker.IsPalindrome("A man, a plan, a canal: Panama")}"); // True
Console.WriteLine($"'hello' is a palindrome: {PalindromeChecker.IsPalindrome("hello")}"); // False
```
This handles common variations nicely! Anything else you'd like to check?

