Sige, narito ang isang Dockerfile para sa PHP-FPM at isang simpleng Nginx config. Kailangan mong magkaroon ng `index.php` sa `src` folder mo.

`Dockerfile`:
```dockerfile
FROM php:8.2-fpm-alpine
WORKDIR /var/www/html
COPY src/ .
RUN chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html
```

`nginx.conf` (ilagay sa tabi ng Dockerfile):
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    index index.php index.html;
    error_log /var/log/nginx/error.log;
    access_log /var/log/nginx/access.log;
    root /var/www/html;

    location ~ \.php$ {
        try_files $uri =404;
        fastcgi_split_path_info ^(.+\.php)(/.+)$;
        fastcgi_pass php:9000;
        fastcgi_index index.php;
        include fastcgi_params;
        fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;
        fastcgi_param PATH_INFO $fastcgi_path_info;
    }

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
    }
}
```

Para mag-run, kailangan mo ng `docker-compose.yml` na nagsasama sa dalawa. Gusto mo bang tulungan kitang gawin 'yon?

