  const handleError = () => setImgError(true);

  const avatarStyle: React.CSSProperties = {
    width: size, height: size, borderRadius: '50%',
    display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center',
    backgroundColor: '#eee', color: '#555', fontSize: size / 2.5,
    fontWeight: 'bold', objectFit: 'cover',
  };

  if (src && !imgError) {
    return <img src={src} alt={alt} style={avatarStyle} onError={handleError} {...props} />;
  }

  return (
    <div style={avatarStyle} {...props}>
      {initials || alt.charAt(0).toUpperCase()}
    </div>
  );
};
```
It handles image loading errors gracefully. You can use it like `<Avatar src="user.jpg" alt="John Doe" initials="JD" />`. How about adding a badge for online status?

Chào bạn! Đây là đoạn mã Express.js cho endpoint "Hello World" bạn cần:

```javascript
